I tried both ways, it doesn't seem to make a difference.

eg running like in #1390

 sess = tf.Session(config=tf.ConfigProto(
             allow_soft_placement=True,
             log_device_placement=False))

     # Start the queue runners.
     tf.train.start_queue_runners(sess=sess)
     init = tf.global_variables_initializer()
     sess.run(init)

or how I posted

  sess = tf.Session(config=tf.ConfigProto(
              allow_soft_placement=True,
              log_device_placement=False))

      # Start the queue runners.
      init = tf.global_variables_initializer()
      sess.run(init)

      tf.train.start_queue_runners(sess=sess)

Doesn't make a difference. Either way the same error appears

body:
I tried both ways, it doesn't seem to make a difference. 

eg running like in #1390
   ```
    sess = tf.Session(config=tf.ConfigProto(
                allow_soft_placement=True,
                log_device_placement=False))

        # Start the queue runners.
        tf.train.start_queue_runners(sess=sess)
        init = tf.global_variables_initializer()
        sess.run(init)


```
or how I posted
  ```
    sess = tf.Session(config=tf.ConfigProto(
                allow_soft_placement=True,
                log_device_placement=False))

        # Start the queue runners.
        init = tf.global_variables_initializer()
        sess.run(init)

        tf.train.start_queue_runners(sess=sess)
```
Doesn't make a difference. Either way the same error appears
